  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Manager",
  "description": "<p><u>Company Overview</u></p>\n<p>Founded in October 2001 with a strong vision to become a premier global leader in the semiconductor equipment industry, GST has emerged as a specialized leader in the environmental and energy sector, successfully listing on KOSDAQ.</p>\n<p>GST manufactures advanced products such as scrubbers, which purify exhaust gases from semiconductor and display manufacturing processes, and chillers, which regulate processing temperatures in Fab equipment. With a commitment to becoming a world-leading technology innovator, GST is dedicated to creating customer value through continuous R&amp;D and the development of next-generation scrubbers and innovative chillers.</p>\n<p>Since 2020, SGST Pte Ltd has operated as our overseas affiliate from South Korea, further expanding our global reach.</p>\n<p><u>Job Responsibilities</u></p>\n<p>· Achieve company objectives through effective planning, setting sales goals, analysing performance data, and projecting future performance.</p>\n<p>· Identify new opportunities, applications, segments, and markets for products and capabilities by understanding our products and recognizing market and customer dynamics.</p>\n<p>· Forecast sales targets, track and record activity on accounts, and help to close deals to meet these targets for the territory.</p>\n<p>· Address customer problems and coordinate with related departments to provide appropriate solutions.</p>\n<p>· Support customer development project management activities, collaborating with marketing teams in Korea.</p>\n<p>· Build relationships with new customers.</p>\n<p>· Create and execute a strategic sales plan to expand the customer base and extend global reach.</p>\n<p>· Meet with potential clients to develop long-lasting relationships by understanding their needs</p>\n<p><u>Requirements</u></p>\n<p>· Bachelor’s degree or higher in a technical or engineering field or marketing.</p>\n<p>· Minimum 7 years of demonstrated success in customer-facing roles, including technical sales/account management experience in the semiconductor industry. Project management experience is a plus.</p>\n<p>· Strong negotiation skills and convincing appearance.</p>\n<p>· Excellent communication, interpersonal, and organizational skills.</p>\n<p>· Strong English verbal and written communication and presentation skills.</p>\n<p>· Team player who works well in complex cross-functional, global business environments.</p>\n<p>· Commitment, initiative, flexibility, and high willingness to travel (&gt;30%).</p>\n<p>· Have your own transportation, making it convenient to visit customer sites.</p>",
